checkaptgpg (0.3) mx; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release. 
  * Support InRelease files (MX-15 & Debian Jessie). 
  * Sections of previously disabled code removed.
  * check_exceptions function recoded to use case command.
  * The --cronjob command line option removed.
  * The /etc/checkaptgpg.conf configuration file nolonger supported.
  * Test added to only allow running script as root.
  * Don't check gpg signatures of Mepis 7, 8, 8.5, 11 CR repos. 
  * New way of assigning GPGKEY, old way didn't work for most non-English locales
  * mx-checkaptgpg.desktop, launch script with su-to-root instead of pkexec.
  * checkaptgpg.desktop (KDE), launch script with su -c instead of pkexec.
  * Removed policykit-1 dependency, added menu dependency.   
  * Online help link updated
 
 -- Kent Mathern <maintainer@mepiscommunity.org>  Wed, 03 Jun 2015 19:31:55 -0400

