checkaptgpg (0.1mcr110+3) mepis; urgency=low
  * checkaptgpg script:
     -lines 61-62, 72-81, 97 changes to also use Release files from /var/lib/apt/lists/partial
       folder. This picks up some keys that were being missed.
     -lines 63-65 added code to not test 'mepiscr' repos.
       This prevents a "No GPG Release signature found." message for those repos
     -lines 124-131 disabled original code that downloaded and installed a key from KEYSERVER
       specified either in CONFFILE (/etc/checkaptgpg.conf) or from within the script
     -lines 133-153 attempt to download and install a key from KEYSERVER using a list of
       keyservers. Stops on first successfull attempt or until all keyservers have been tried.
   * debian/dirs 
      -added leading slash '/' for etc and usr/bin
      -added /usr, /usr/share, /usr/share/applications, /usr/share/pixmaps    

 -- kent <kent@mepis1>  Fri, 22 Apr 2011 13:05:14 -0400

checkaptgpg (0.1mcr110+2) mepis; urgency=low

  * checkaptgpg script:
  *  line 110 disabled KEYSERVER=hkp://wwwkeys.eu.pgp.net
  *  line 111 added KEYSERVER=keys.gnupg.net
  *  line 135, removed 'read -e'command  which causes error in M11
      and combined prompt and read into single command using 'read -p'
  * checkaptgpg-root.desktop deleted - not needed, single menu entry works fine 
  * debian/install added leading slash '/' to install paths
  * debian/manpage.1.ex deleted
  * debian/menu deleted - not needed, checkaptgpg.desktop provides a menu entry

